    "extras": [
      "November to March is the cleanest all-round window: Cape Coast and Wli stay less slippery, and Mole's grass is shorter for easier wildlife sightings.",
      "Castle visits are guided and emotionally heavy; many travelers prefer doing Cape Coast first thing and leaving beach or Elmina time afterward to decompress.",
      "Book the Tamale-Accra domestic leg as early as possible if your dates are fixed, because it is the single highest-impact time saver in this itinerary.",
      "STC and VIP buses are worth the small premium over a full tro-tro for the long Accra-Cape Coast and Kumasi-Tamale stretches.",
      "Outside Accra, carry small cash notes for tro-tros, community guides, and museum add-ons because card acceptance is inconsistent.",
      "Mole and Wli both reward early starts: wildlife is better before the heat builds, and waterfall or mountain hikes feel far easier before noon."
    ],
